textBeforeTable: Star San Marino - A blast from the past with a new age twist. The vintage Roc that started it all meets Innova's high tech Star plastic to form the Star San Marino Roc. Star Rancho - new in May 2012. The Star Rancho Roc was previously reserved for fundraising only, but not any longer. A long time favorite of Pros and Ams alike, the Rancho Roc has earned its place among Innova's premier line of plastic. KC Pro Roc - is more stiff. DX Bottom Stamped - pictured is an Xcaliber Bottom Stamped disc Speed 4, Glide 4, Turn 0, Fade 3 It is a great choice for an experienced player's utility disc, hyzer shots, anhyzer shots, turnover shots when worn, sidearm approaches, and players who like to carry several versions of the same disc in various states of wear. The Innova KC-Pro ROC is simply the best, most versatile mid range driver Innova makes. It provides accuracy at any range. This disc can take and hold the angle of release, even into a headwind. It can be used for driving, upshots, straight shots, hyzer shots or anhyzers. The Roc ages gradually and predictably, becoming an excellent slow turning disc as it wears. If you’re not sure what golf disc to throw, choose the Roc, just like the 14 out of 15 Innova Pros that have at least one if not 4 or 5 Rocs in their bag.
